{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":332,"text":"\"Iran is Israel's best friend,"},{"time":2402,"text":"and we do not intend to change our position"},{"time":5111,"text":"in relation to Tehran.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":8591,"text":"Believe it or not, this is a quote"},{"time":10314,"text":"from an Israeli prime minister,"},{"time":12513,"text":"but it's not Ben-Gurion or Golda Meir"},{"time":14957,"text":"from the era of the Shah."},{"time":17150,"text":"It's actually from Yitzhak Rabin."},{"time":19568,"text":"The year is 1987."},{"time":22054,"text":"Ayatollah Khomeini is still alive,"},{"time":23975,"text":"and much like Ahmadinejad today,"},{"time":25913,"text":"he's using the worst rhetoric against Israel."},{"time":28813,"text":"Yet, Rabin referred to Iran"},{"time":31692,"text":"as a geostrategic friend."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34942,"text":"Today, when we hear the threats of war"},{"time":37638,"text":"and the high rhetoric,"},{"time":39044,"text":"we're oftentimes led to believe"},{"time":40675,"text":"that this is yet another one of those unsolvable"},{"time":43958,"text":"Middle Eastern conflicts"},{"time":45833,"text":"with roots as old as the region itself."},{"time":49561,"text":"Nothing could be further from the truth,"},{"time":53450,"text":"and I hope today to show you why that is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57482,"text":"The relations between the Iranian and the Jewish people"},{"time":59820,"text":"throughout history has actually been quite positive,"},{"time":62300,"text":"starting in 539 B.C.,"},{"time":64700,"text":"when King Cyrus the Great of Persia"},{"time":66589,"text":"liberated the Jewish people from their Babylonian captivity."},{"time":70283,"text":"A third of the Jewish population"},{"time":72754,"text":"stayed in Babylonia."},{"time":74320,"text":"They're today's Iraqi Jews."},{"time":76570,"text":"A third migrated to Persia."},{"time":79676,"text":"They're today's Iranian Jews,"},{"time":81752,"text":"still 25,000 of them living in Iran,"},{"time":84783,"text":"making them the largest Jewish community"},{"time":86695,"text":"in the Middle East outside of Israel itself."},{"time":89943,"text":"And a third returned to historic Palestine,"},{"time":92574,"text":"did the second rebuilding of the Temple in Jerusalem,"},{"time":95625,"text":"financed, incidentally, by Persian tax money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100774,"text":"But even in modern times,"},{"time":102860,"text":"relations have been close at times."},{"time":105305,"text":"Rabin's statement was a reflection"},{"time":108106,"text":"of decades of security and intelligence collaboration"},{"time":112064,"text":"between the two, which in turn"},{"time":114600,"text":"was born out of perception of common threats."},{"time":118597,"text":"Both states feared the Soviet Union"},{"time":121412,"text":"and strong Arab states such as Egypt and Iraq."},{"time":126559,"text":"And, in addition, the Israeli doctrine of the periphery,"},{"time":130800,"text":"the idea that Israel's security was best achieved"},{"time":134092,"text":"by creating alliances with the non-Arab states"},{"time":138170,"text":"in the periphery of the region"},{"time":140076,"text":"in order to balance the Arab states in its vicinity."},{"time":144965,"text":"Now, from the Shah's perspective, though,"},{"time":147433,"text":"he wanted to keep this as secret as possible,"},{"time":151087,"text":"so when Yitzhak Rabin, for instance,"},{"time":153335,"text":"traveled to Iran in the '70s,"},{"time":155227,"text":"he usually wore a wig"},{"time":156675,"text":"so that no one would recognize him."},{"time":159086,"text":"The Iranians built a special tarmac"},{"time":161521,"text":"at the airport in Tehran, far away from the central terminal,"},{"time":164773,"text":"so that no one would notice the large number"},{"time":167078,"text":"of Israeli planes shuttling between Tel Aviv and Tehran."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172499,"text":"Now, did all of this end with the Islamic revolution"},{"time":175686,"text":"in 1979?"},{"time":178639,"text":"In spite of the very clear anti-Israeli ideology"},{"time":181706,"text":"of the new regime, the geopolitical logic"},{"time":185099,"text":"for their collaboration lived on,"},{"time":187703,"text":"because they still had common threats."},{"time":190515,"text":"And when Iraq invaded Iran in 1980,"},{"time":193544,"text":"Israel feared an Iraqi victory"},{"time":196034,"text":"and actively helped Iran by selling it arms"},{"time":198785,"text":"and providing it with spare parts"},{"time":201037,"text":"for Iran's American weaponry"},{"time":203197,"text":"at a moment when Iran was very vulnerable"},{"time":206913,"text":"because of an American arms embargo"},{"time":209415,"text":"that Israel was more than happy to violate."},{"time":212403,"text":"In fact, back in the 1980s,"},{"time":215161,"text":"it was Israel that lobbied Washington"},{"time":217970,"text":"to talk to Iran, to sell arms to Iran,"},{"time":222079,"text":"and not pay attention to Iran's anti-Israeli ideology."},{"time":227703,"text":"And this, of course, climaxed"},{"time":229642,"text":"in the Iran-Contra scandal of the 1980s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234293,"text":"But with the end of the Cold War"},{"time":236293,"text":"came also the end of the Israeli-Iranian cold peace."},{"time":240731,"text":"Suddenly, the two common threats"},{"time":243091,"text":"that had pushed them closer together throughout decades,"},{"time":246144,"text":"more or less evaporated."},{"time":248590,"text":"The Soviet Union collapsed,"},{"time":250552,"text":"Iraq was defeated,"},{"time":252244,"text":"and a new environment was created in the region"},{"time":254325,"text":"in which both of them felt more secure,"},{"time":256665,"text":"but they were also now left unchecked."},{"time":259585,"text":"Without Iraq balancing Iran,"},{"time":262700,"text":"Iran could now become a threat,"},{"time":264878,"text":"some in Israel argued."},{"time":267410,"text":"In fact, the current dynamic"},{"time":270355,"text":"that you see between Iran and Israel"},{"time":272447,"text":"has its roots more so"},{"time":274542,"text":"in the geopolitical reconfiguration of the region"},{"time":277195,"text":"after the Cold War"},{"time":278984,"text":"than in the events of 1979,"},{"time":281484,"text":"because at this point, Iran and Israel"},{"time":284181,"text":"emerge as two of the most powerful states in the region,"},{"time":288069,"text":"and rather than viewing each other"},{"time":289312,"text":"as potential security partners,"},{"time":291788,"text":"they increasingly came to view each other"},{"time":294000,"text":"as rivals and competitors."},{"time":297558,"text":"So Israel, who in the 1980s"},{"time":299359,"text":"lobbied for and improved U.S.-Iran relations"},{"time":302884,"text":"now feared a U.S.-Iran rapprochement,"},{"time":306267,"text":"thinking that it would come"},{"time":307561,"text":"at Israel's security interests' expense,"},{"time":311223,"text":"and instead sought to put Iran"},{"time":313355,"text":"in increased isolation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315889,"text":"Ironically, this was happening at a time"},{"time":318817,"text":"when Iran was more interested"},{"time":320884,"text":"in peacemaking with Washington"},{"time":323034,"text":"than to see to Israel's destruction."},{"time":326469,"text":"Iran had put itself in isolation"},{"time":328309,"text":"because of its radicalism,"},{"time":330176,"text":"and after having helped the United States indirectly"},{"time":333095,"text":"in the war against Iraq in 1991,"},{"time":335367,"text":"the Iranians were hoping"},{"time":337323,"text":"that they would be rewarded by being included"},{"time":341225,"text":"in the post-war security architecture of the region."},{"time":345955,"text":"But Washington chose to ignore Iran's outreach,"},{"time":349507,"text":"as it would a decade later in Afghanistan,"},{"time":351943,"text":"and instead moved to intensify Iran's isolation,"},{"time":356138,"text":"and it is at this point, around 1993, '94,"},{"time":359372,"text":"that Iran begins to translate"},{"time":362084,"text":"its anti-Israeli ideology"},{"time":364311,"text":"into operational policy."},{"time":366706,"text":"The Iranians believed that whatever they did,"},{"time":368985,"text":"even if they moderated their policies,"},{"time":371295,"text":"the U.S. would continue to seek Iran's isolation,"},{"time":374597,"text":"and the only way Iran could compel Washington"},{"time":378251,"text":"to change its position was by imposing a cost"},{"time":381547,"text":"on the U.S. if it didn't."},{"time":384860,"text":"The easiest target was the peace process,"},{"time":388950,"text":"and now the Iranian ideological bark"},{"time":391327,"text":"was to be accompanied by a nonconventional bite,"},{"time":395566,"text":"and Iran began supporting extensively"},{"time":399543,"text":"Palestinian Islamist groups that it previously"},{"time":402242,"text":"had shunned."},{"time":405633,"text":"In some ways, this sounds paradoxical,"},{"time":408848,"text":"but according to Martin Indyk"},{"time":410968,"text":"of the Clinton administration,"},{"time":412841,"text":"the Iranians had not gotten it entirely wrong,"},{"time":415740,"text":"because the more peace there would be"},{"time":417281,"text":"between Israel and Palestine,"},{"time":419444,"text":"the U.S. believed, the more Iran would get isolated."},{"time":422807,"text":"The more Iran got isolated, the more peace there would be."},{"time":425943,"text":"So according to Indyk, and these are his words,"},{"time":428391,"text":"the Iranians had an interest to do us in"},{"time":431579,"text":"on the peace process"},{"time":433246,"text":"in order to defeat our policy of containment."},{"time":436958,"text":"To defeat our policy of containment,"},{"time":439324,"text":"not about ideology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443310,"text":"But throughout even the worst times of their entanglement,"},{"time":447015,"text":"all sides have reached out to each other."},{"time":450278,"text":"Netanyahu, when he got elected in 1996,"},{"time":453547,"text":"reached out to the Iranians to see"},{"time":455343,"text":"if there were any ways that"},{"time":457046,"text":"the doctrine of the periphery could be resurrected."},{"time":460235,"text":"Tehran was not interested."},{"time":462705,"text":"A few years later, the Iranians sent"},{"time":465670,"text":"a comprehensive negotiation proposal to the Bush administration,"},{"time":469129,"text":"a proposal that revealed that there was some potential"},{"time":473137,"text":"of getting Iran and Israel back on terms again."},{"time":477000,"text":"The Bush administration did not even respond."},{"time":480260,"text":"All sides have never missed an opportunity"},{"time":483080,"text":"to miss an opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488897,"text":"But this is not an ancient conflict."},{"time":493569,"text":"This is not even an ideological conflict."},{"time":496528,"text":"The ebbs and flows of hostility"},{"time":499322,"text":"have not shifted with ideological zeal,"},{"time":502598,"text":"but rather with changes in the geopolitical landscape."},{"time":505200,"text":"When Iran and Israel's security imperatives"},{"time":507531,"text":"dictated collaboration, they did so"},{"time":510233,"text":"in spite of lethal ideological opposition to each other."},{"time":513809,"text":"When Iran's ideological impulses collided"},{"time":516725,"text":"with its strategic interests,"},{"time":518955,"text":"the strategic interests always prevailed."},{"time":522618,"text":"This is good news, because it means"},{"time":525611,"text":"that neither war nor enmity"},{"time":528197,"text":"is a foregone conclusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531867,"text":"But some want war."},{"time":534422,"text":"Some believe or say that it's 1938,"},{"time":537626,"text":"Iran is Germany,"},{"time":539538,"text":"and Ahmadinejad is Hitler."},{"time":542704,"text":"If we accept this to be true,"},{"time":544569,"text":"that indeed it is 1938, Iran is Germany,"},{"time":547921,"text":"Ahmadinejad is Hitler,"},{"time":550328,"text":"then the question we have to ask ourself is,"},{"time":553163,"text":"who wishes to play the role of Neville Chamberlain?"},{"time":556976,"text":"Who will risk peace?"},{"time":559842,"text":"This is an analogy that is deliberately aimed"},{"time":562456,"text":"at eliminating diplomacy,"},{"time":565216,"text":"and when you eliminate diplomacy,"},{"time":567628,"text":"you make war inevitable."},{"time":570717,"text":"In an ideological conflict, there can be no truce,"},{"time":573832,"text":"no draw, no compromise,"},{"time":575997,"text":"only victory or defeat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579279,"text":"But rather than making war inevitable"},{"time":582469,"text":"by viewing this as ideological,"},{"time":585673,"text":"we would be wise to seek ways"},{"time":587712,"text":"to make peace possible."},{"time":590700,"text":"Iran and Israel's conflict is a new phenomenon,"},{"time":594196,"text":"only a few decades old"},{"time":596186,"text":"in a history of 2,500 years,"},{"time":598812,"text":"and precisely because its roots are geopolitical,"},{"time":602799,"text":"it means that solutions can be found,"},{"time":605639,"text":"compromises can be struck,"},{"time":608326,"text":"however difficult it yet may be."},{"time":611145,"text":"After all, it was Yitzhak Rabin himself who said,"},{"time":615137,"text":"\"You don't make peace with your friends."},{"time":618123,"text":"You make it with your enemies.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":620503,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621938,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}